item.description:
ssh connect $ ssh userNameOnServer@&lt;IP_ADDRESS_OF_SERVER&gt;  connects via ssh to the server on port 22. If the port is not 22, add portnumber via argument -p;
$ ssh userNameOnServer@&lt;IP_ADDRESS_OF_SERVER&gt; -p &lt;PORT_NBR&gt;  generate ssh key Generate your key;
 $ ssh-keygen -t rsa  Follow the prompts - choose default location where keys will be saved.
A ~/.ssh directory hase been created with your keys in it. The .pub is your public key an the other file is your private key.
